## Mnemix — Cross-Session Memory (MANDATORY)

All agents have access to episodic memory that persists across conversations.
Mnemix records bugs fixed, decisions made, patterns discovered, and errors resolved.

**Every agent session must — this is mandatory, do not skip:**
1. **Start** with `{{mnemix.binary}} --store {{mnemix.store_path}} recall --scope {{mnemix.scope}}` to check prior context
2. **End** by persisting a memory with `{{mnemix.binary}} --store {{mnemix.store_path}} remember ...`

Recall prior `decision`, `fact`, `procedure`, `warning`, and `summary` memories that could affect the task.
Record new memory only when it will help a future session avoid rediscovery, repeat a useful procedure, or preserve a meaningful decision.

Skipping recall means repeating mistakes from prior sessions. This is not optional.
The store is local, gitignored, and per-developer. It does not affect project files.
See [skills/mnemix-memory/SKILL.md](skills/mnemix-memory/SKILL.md) for full CLI reference.

